title: Cheryl finally confirms pregnancy with first official baby bump pic
text:
L'OREAL SPOT THE BUMP: Cheryl has officially revealed her bump for the first time 
The former Girls Aloud singer has sported a huge baby bump over the last few months, although never spoke out about expecting a child with boyfriend Liam Payne. 
But now, Cheryl has confirmed her pregnancy by cradling her bump in a massive ad campaign. 
The 33-year-old appears in a new group ad for The Prince's Trust and L'Oreal Paris, and can be seen affectionately holding a huge bump - sparking speculation she's just days away from giving birth. 
L'OREAL BLOOMING LOVELY: Cheryl cradled her tummy in the gorgeous snap Cheryl's sexiest pictures A selection of pictures covering the highlights of Cheryl Cole's career. 1 / 93 “My hope is that this partnership will help young people feel accepted and valued for who they are” Cheryl 
The Fight For This Love singer is seen wearing a stretchy bodycon dress that shows off her pregnancy curves to perfection as she stands in the background of the group photo. 
Cheryl appears alongside stars including Katie Piper, Helen Mirren and Louisa Johnson in the ad, which has been released to launch The Prince's Trust and L'Oreal Paris' three year campaign to help young people with self-doubt. 
The campaign, called All Worth It, aims to turn young people's self-doubt into self-worth. 
GETTY PARENTS TO BE: Liam and Cheryl are weeks away from welcoming their first baby Bump It Up: The Most Popular Pregnant Celeb Photos Thursday, 2nd February 2017 See a list of celebrities who posed naked and pregnant for magazines and more scandalous nude celeb baby bump photos. 1 / 20 
The Prince's Trust and L'Oreal have chosen 15 ambassadors for the cause - Cheryl, Helen, Katie, Louisa, blogger Gary Thompson, model Chez Rust, beauty blogger Kaushal, bloggers Jordan Bone, Emily Canham, Victoria Magrath and Amena Khan, YouTube star Marcus Butler, model Neelam Gill, TV presenter AJ Oduhu and model Jade Sezer. 
Cheryl said: "Young people are currently facing more and more problems with self-confidence and we have to address these issues as a real priority. 
"My hope is that this partnership will help young people feel accepted and valued for who they are and make sure that they get the support they need to make the most out of life."
